4. Version number guide lines
-----------------------------

The scheme for the 7-Zip-JBinding version numbers is :

	<7-Zip/p7zip version> - <7-Zip-JBinding version><release stage>

7-Zip/p7zip version - version of the underlying 7-Zip and p7zip libraries.

7-Zip-JBinding version - version of 7-Zip-JBinding base on the specified 7-Zip/p7zip version, beginning from 1 

release stage:
	- 'alpha' - alpha release: substantion part of the functionality included, not stable. For testing purposes only.
	- 'rc' - release candidate: all functionality included, not stable. For testing purposes only.
	- '' - release considered stable. For generally use.

Examples:
	 4.65-1alpha - Alpha release #1 based on 7-Zip/p7zip version 4.65
	 4.66-1rc - Release candidate #2 based on 7-Zip/p7zip version 4.66
	 4.66-2 - Stable release based on 7-Zip/p7zip version 4.66


5. Compile under Linux

a) Check out or download source package
b) Extract into some <src> directory

